# Development Rule

- Always up to date
- Always respect DDD princibles
- Always respect best practices in software design
- Always respect particularly around Clean Code
- Always respect SOLID principles
- Always respect TDD practices
- Always respect Object-Oriented Design
- Always respect Domain-Driven Design (DDD)
- Always respect to build a scalable, maintainable, and extendable
- Existing tests should never be changed. If the feature has changed, it should be changed.


# Create a new relase rule
## Increase version from package.json
Increase version of an annotated tag `"version": "x.y.z",`

## Update dependencies
npm update

## Update version in package.json
## package-lock.json will be updated automatically

## Commit changes
git add package.json package-lock.json
git commit -m "Bump version to x.y.z"

## Create tag
git tag -a vx.y.z -m "Release version x.y.z"

## Push changes and tags
git push && git push --tags
